While the AssetManager is in loading progress and the app is deactivated in ios (with air sdk 3.9), the app would crash. The problem is the loader's complete handler can't be paused when a app is deactivated, while the stage3d api is called.
The problem appears to be here:
texture = Texture.fromBitmap(asset as Bitmap, mUseMipMaps, false, mScaleFactor);
texture = Texture.fromAtfData(bytes, mScaleFactor, mUseMipMaps, onComplete);

When certain sprite coordinates are off-screen, the scissor rectangle is calculated incorrectly.

The problem appears to be here:

```
            // convert to pixel coordinates (matrix transformation ends up in range [-1, 1])
            MatrixUtil.transformCoords(mProjectionMatrix, rect.x, rect.y, sPoint);
            sRectangle.x = sPoint.x > -1 ? (( sPoint.x + 1) / 2) * width  : 0.0;
            sRectangle.y = sPoint.y > -1 ? ((-sPoint.y + 1) / 2) * height : 0.0;

            MatrixUtil.transformCoords(mProjectionMatrix, rect.right, rect.bottom, sPoint);
            sRectangle.right  = sPoint.x < 1 ? (( sPoint.x + 1) / 2) * width  : width;
            sRectangle.bottom = sPoint.y < 1 ? ((-sPoint.y + 1) / 2) * height : height;
```

Because the y coordinate is inverted, the 0.0 and height should be switched. This seems to fix the bug for me:

```
            // convert to pixel coordinates (matrix transformation ends up in range [-1, 1])
            MatrixUtil.transformCoords(mProjectionMatrix, rect.x, rect.y, sPoint);
            sRectangle.x = sPoint.x > -1 ? (( sPoint.x + 1) / 2) * width  : 0.0;
            sRectangle.y = sPoint.y > -1 ? ((-sPoint.y + 1) / 2) * height : height;

            MatrixUtil.transformCoords(mProjectionMatrix, rect.right, rect.bottom, sPoint);
            sRectangle.right  = sPoint.x < 1 ? (( sPoint.x + 1) / 2) * width  : width;
            sRectangle.bottom = sPoint.y < 1 ? ((-sPoint.y + 1) / 2) * height : 0.0;
```

Noticed an error when using quads with just a color, i.e. no texture. If I have a non-textured quad with normal blend mode directly underneath a non-textured quad with say blend mode Multiply, the top quad is rendered with normal blend mode.  I believe this is because isStateChange doesn't properly handle this case.  I've fixed it in my local copy of Starling with the following lines (sorry, I don't know how to use Git properly yet to do pull requests).  It fixed my specific error but it is possible there are others I haven't considered.

```
    public function isStateChange(tinted:Boolean, parentAlpha:Number, texture:Texture, 
                                  smoothing:String, blendMode:String, numQuads:int=1):Boolean
    {
        if (mNumQuads == 0) return false;
        else if (mNumQuads + numQuads > 8192) return true; // maximum buffer size
        //else if (mTexture == null && texture == null) return false;
        else if (mTexture == null && texture == null) return this.blendMode != blendMode;
        else if (mTexture != null && texture != null)
            return mTexture.base != texture.base ||
                   mTexture.repeat != texture.repeat ||
                   mSmoothing != smoothing ||
                   mTinted != (tinted || parentAlpha != 1.0) ||
                   this.blendMode != blendMode;
        else return true;
    }
```

